1 olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
2 clove garlic
1 packet chicken thigh
½ onion
1 tsp honey
1 cucumber
1 tomato
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet mayonnaise
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
¼ cup vinegar (white wine or red wine)
1 packet Greek salad cheese/feta cheese

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut
the potato into bite-sized chunks, then place on a
lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with
the chicken-style stock powder and season with
salt. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast
until tender, 20-25 minutes.

While the potatoes are roasting, finely chop the
garlic. In a medium bowl, combine the garlic,
Aussie spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Add
the chicken thigh, then season with salt and
pepper. Turn to coat and set aside.

Thinly slice the red onion (see ingredients). In
a small bowl, combine the vinegar and a good
pinch of salt and sugar. Scrunch the onion in your
hands, then add to the pickling liquid with just
enough water to cover the onion. Set aside.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over a medium-high heat. Cook the chicken until
browned, 2 minutes each side. Remove the pan
from the heat, then add the honey and turn the
chicken to coat. Transfer the chicken to a second
lined oven tray and bake until cooked through,
8-12 minutes (depending on size).

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer
pink inside.

While the chicken is cooking, finely chop the
cucumber and tomato. Drain the pickled onion
(reserve some pickling liquid for the dressing). In
a medium bowl, combine the cucumber, tomato,
pickled onion, mixed salad leaves, a dash of the
pickling liquid and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to
taste and toss to coat.

Slice the golden chicken. Divide the chicken,
roasted potatoes and Greek salad between plates.
Crumble the cheese over the salad. Serve with
the mayonnaise.